      "writtenOn": "2026-06-29T17:45:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[error] Line 391: Unnumbered HID reports are handled as if byte 0 were always a report ID. For descriptors without a Report ID, loc.reportId remains 0, so input reports whose first payload byte is non-zero are ignored and bitValue() reads the wrong byte by skipping byte 0. Track whether numbered reports are used and only require/skip the ID byte when the descriptor actually declares a Report ID.",
      "revId": "2297172e3c04549bb267b9f8e699f8840dd15630",
